{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σκέπ-τομαι</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.652, 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1095 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], and <i>Ionic dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.37, +others, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προγνωστικόν” 2, 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 7.92 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but <i>Attic dialect</i> writers (before [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] hardly ever have the <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i> σκέπτομαι, ἐσκεπτόμην (except [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 185b, Alcaeus2.140a; in 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.66 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], Bauer restored <i>pluperfect</i> προὔσκεπτο), but use σκοπῶ or σκοποῦμαι as <i>present</i>, and take the other tenses from σκέπτομαι, <i>future</i> σκέψομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 29, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.40, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>aorist</i> ἐσκεψάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 229, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1028, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 206 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.38, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>perfect</i> ἔσκεμμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 147, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 24, etc.: compare σκοπέω:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —but the <i>perfect</i> is used also in <i>passive</i> sense, as also some other tenses, see below [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.4. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>look</b> <b>about carefully, spy</b>, σκεψάμενος δ᾽ ἐς νῆα θοὴν ἅμα καὶ μεθ᾽ ἑταίρους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.247; so σκέψασθε δ᾽ ἐς τόνδ᾽ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 943: with _accusative_, σκέπτετ᾽ ὀϊστῶν τε ῥοῖζον καὶ δοῦπον ἀκόντων\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>he looked after</b> the whistling of the darts (so as to shun them), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.361; σκέπτεο δὴ νῦν ἄλλον 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1095; σκεπτόμενος τοὺς νεκρούς 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.37 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σκέψαι.. βόστρυχον τριχός <b>look well at</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 229; τὴν ἔγχελυν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 889; κλόνον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 206 (Lyric poetry); τὰ ἔνδον 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 4.4.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τιν᾽ ἐς δὲ μωρίαν ἐσκεμμένοι <b>looking into you and seeing.. </b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 147 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: followed by an Interrog., σκέπτεο νῦν.., αἴ κεν ἴδηαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.652; σ. πόθεν ἡ στάσις, ἢ τίς ὁ θρύλλος Batrachomyomachia 135; τί εἴη τὸ κωλῦον 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.5.20; εἰ εἴη ἴχνη ἀνθρώπων [prev. work] 7.3.42 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>look at, examine</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.196 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σκέψασθε, παῖδες <b>look</b>, lads! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 419. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>examine</b>, τῷ δακτύλῳ τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ γυναικείης φύσιος” 7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> later of the mind, <b>view, examine, consider</b>, σκέψασθε.. τὴν τύχην δυοῖν βροτοῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1028; σκέψαι δὲ τοῦτο πρῶτον [prev. author] “OT” 584; ὃ πολλάκις ἐσκεψάμην 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.38, etc.; τὸ δίκαιον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 494 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μηδὲν ἐσκέφθαι δίκ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.192; πρὸς ἑαυτόν τι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 95e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ τῶνδε σκέψαι <b>from</b> these facts, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.6.38, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.17; περί τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 185c, “Cra.” 401a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σκέψασθαι ἀπὸ τῶν παίδων <b>judge</b> by what children do, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 576; ἐν σοὶ σκεψώμεθα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 239b: _absolutely_, σκέψασθέ νυν ἄμεινον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1291; σκεψώμεθα δή 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 802 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σκέψασθε δέ· <b>only consider</b>, to call people's attention to a point, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.41, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.143: followed by a clause with οἷος, ὁποῖος, ὡς, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1014, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1077, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 1377, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; by ὅτῳ τρόπῳ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.107 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; by πῶς.., πόθεν.., πότερον.. ἤ.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.5.22, 5.4.7, 3.2.20, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; by εἰ, <b>consider</b> whether or no, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 442, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 29, “Eq.” 1141, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.22; in full, σ. τοῦτο, εἰ.. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 584; τί ἐστιν ἡ ἀρετὴ σκεπτόμεθα 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1103b28. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> rarely, <b>think</b> or <b>deem</b> a thing to be so and so, καλλίω θάνατον σκεψάμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 854c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>think of beforehand, provide</b>, σκεπτόμεθα τἀναγκαῖ᾽ ἑκάστης ἡμέρας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 120; τὸ συμφέρον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 342a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>prepare, premeditate</b>, λόγους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.158; εἴ τι χρήσιμον ἐσκεμμένος ἥκει [prev. author] 1.1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>plan</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.63. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <i>perfect</i> in <i>passive</i> sense, πάντα ἐσκεμμένα ἡτοίμασται <b>with consideration</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 7.62 \">Refs</a>]; σκοπεῖτε οὖν. Answ. ἔσκεπται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 369b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.3.8, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.191, 61.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also 3 <i>future</i> <i>passive</i> ἐσκέψεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 392c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>aorist</i> ἐσκέφθην, ες τὸ σκεφθῆναι for <b>observation</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ τέχνης” 11; \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist 2</i> and <i>future</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2 ἐσκέπην \">Refs</a>] (ἐπ-), σκεπήσομαι (ἐπι-), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Num.1.19, LXX.1Ki.20.18. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G9100","accentedUnicode":"σκέπτομαι","shortDef":"to look about","mediumDef":"to look about","stepGloss":"to look about","stepTransliteration":"skeptomai","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}